                    <state type="group" source="#bib1483-2"/>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1483">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1483">Shirin</persName> and her two children
          were martyrs from <placeName>Beth Zadoq</placeName>. She was baking bread when she learned
          of 12000 martyrs under <persName>Yazdegerd II</persName>. She took herself and her children
          before the governor and confessed her Christian faith to him. She and her children were
          decapitated.</note>
